Project Report 
Overview

This project is a machine learning-based real estate price prediction system designed for Karachi housing data. It predicts property prices using structured features like area, location, bedrooms, bathrooms, and
property type. The system is deployed as an interactive Streamlit web application for real-time predictions.

It demonstrates a complete end-to-end ML pipeline: data collection → EDA → feature engineering → model training → evaluation → deployment.

Dataset

The dataset consists of 189 real estate listings collected from publicly available sources.

Features:
Property Type (House / Flat)
Bedrooms
Bathrooms
Area (sqft)
Location
Furnishing Status
Price (PKR)
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Key insights:

Houses are generally more expensive than flats
Location has a major impact on price
Price distribution is highly skewed
Furnished properties are costlier
Area and price contain outliers
Feature Engineering

To improve model performance:

One-hot encoding for categorical variables
Created:
price_per_sqft
total_rooms
Applied log transformation:
log_price
log_area
Standardized numerical features using StandardScaler

Models Used
1. Linear Regression
R²: 0.78 – 0.83
Simple but struggles with non-linearity
2. Decision Tree
R²: 0.86
Captures non-linear relationships
3. Random Forest  (Best Model)
R²: 0.959
Best performance due to ensemble learning
Handles outliers and complexity well
Final Model Selection

Random Forest Regressor

Highest accuracy
Most stable predictions
Best generalization

