 Questions

1. What is my project about?

It is a machine learning system that predicts house prices in Karachi using features like area, location, and property type, deployed using Streamlit.

2. Why did i choose this project?

Because real estate pricing is a real-world regression problem and it combines data science, ML, and deployment — a full-stack ML experience.

3. What type of problem is this?

It is a supervised regression problem.

Data Questions

4. What dataset did you use?

A manually compiled dataset of 189 Karachi property listings.

5. What challenges did you face in the data?
Skewed price distribution
Outliers (luxury properties)
Small dataset size
Mixed categorical + numerical data

Feature Engineering

6. Why did you use log transformation?

To reduce skewness in price and stabilize variance for better model learning.

7. Why did i create price per sqft?

Because it normalizes property value and helps capture real market pricing trends.

8. Why encoding categorical variables?

Machine learning models require numerical input, so we converted categories into numeric form.

Model Questions

9. Why Random Forest performed best?

Because it:

Combines multiple decision trees
Reduces overfitting
Captures non-linear relationships
Handles outliers better

10. Difference between Linear Regression and Random Forest?

Linear Regression	Random Forest
Assumes linear relation	Handles non-linear patterns
Sensitive to outliers	Robust to outliers
Simple model	Ensemble of trees
Lower accuracy	Higher accuracy

11. Why Decision Tree overfits?

Because it keeps splitting data until it memorizes patterns, instead of generalizing.

Evaluation Questions

12. What is R² score?

It measures how well the model explains variance in data (closer to 1 = better).

13. Why is MSE used?

It measures average squared difference between predicted and actual values.

